'''El Hadji Malick Diouf''' (born 29 December 2004) is a Senegalese<ref>{{Cite web |last=Demba |first=Varore |date=24 April 2024 |title=El Hadji Malick Diouf: "Depuis tout petit, j'ai baigné dans la culture sénégalaise" - Football |url=https://sportnewsafrica.com/news-football/montpellier-modibo-sagnan-depuis-tout-petit-jai-baigne-dans-la-culture-malienne/ |access-date=7 August 2025 |website=Sport News Africa |language=fr-FR}}</ref> professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] or [[left wing-back]] for [[EFL Championship]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] and the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].<ref name=SK>{{cite news|url=https://en.slavia.cz/clanek.asp?id=El-Hadji-Malick-Diouf-Joins-Slavia-1191|title=El Hadji Malick Diouf joins Slavia|publisher=SK Slavia Prague|date=11 January 2024|access-date=1 March 2024}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Tromsø===
Born in [[Dakar]], Diouf began his footballing journey at just 13 years old with the Galaxy Football Academy.<ref>{{cite web | title=El Hadji Malick Diouf Player Profile: Career, Playing Style and Potential | website=Football Park | date=30 August 2025 | url=https://footballpark.com/football-blogs/el-hadji-malick-diouf-player-profile-career-playing-style-and-potential | access-date=23 September 2025}}</ref> After a successful stint of four years, he joined the Academie Mawade Wade.<ref name="eight">{{cite web | title=Eight things you didn't know about El Hadji Malick Diouf | website=West Ham United F.C. | date=15 July 2025 | url=https://www.whufc.com/news/eight-things-you-didnt-know-about-el-hadji-malick-diouf | access-date=16 July 2025}}</ref> On 21 February 2023, after a successful trial, Diouf signed with Norwegian side [[Tromsø IL|Tromsø]].<ref name=til>{{cite news|url=https://www.til.no/nyheter/diouf-har-signert|title=Diouf har signert|language=no|publisher=Tromsø IL|date=21 February 2023|access-date=1 March 2024}}</ref>  After a slow start to the season, with little game time, the latter half of the season saw Diouf getting regular game time, ending the season with twenty-one appearances, and three goals for the club.<ref name=nff>{{NFF|3996490}}</ref>

===Slavia Prague===
In January 2024, Diouf signed for Czech top flight club [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] on a four-and-a-half-year contract.<ref name=SK/> His first goal for the club came in his debut game, against [[MFK Karviná|Karviná]].<ref name=sw>{{soccerway|el-hadji-malick-diouf/895893}}</ref> In the [[2024–25 SK Slavia Prague season|2024–25 season for Slavia Prague]], Diouf  played as a left wing-back as they won the [[2024–25 Czech First League|Czech First League]] title. He scored five goals in the first eight games and in 24 league appearances for the season, scored seven goals and made three assists.<ref name=eight/>

===West Ham United===
On 15 July 2025, Diouf signed for [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] on a long-term contract for a fee of £19m.<ref>{{cite web | title=West Ham United sign Senegal international El Hadji Malick Diouf | website=West Ham United F.C. | date=15 July 2025 | url=https://www.whufc.com/news/west-ham-united-sign-senegal-international-el-hadji-malick-diouf | access-date=15 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=El Hadji Malick Diouf joins West Ham from Slavia Prague for £19m | website=BBC Sport | date=15 July 2025 | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cddzpd1eev7o | access-date=17 July 2025}}</ref> 
On 16 August 2025, he made his competitive debut, in a 3–0 loss to [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] at the [[Stadium of Light]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Taylor |first=Louise |date=2025-08-16 |title=Mayenda sparks stunning Sunderland start to increase Potter's West Ham pain |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/aug/16/sunderland-west-ham-premier-league-match-report |access-date=2025-08-18 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

==International career==
Diouf made his debut for the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]] on 9 September 2024 in a [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification Group L|Africa Cup of Nations qualifier]] against [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]] at the [[Bingu National Stadium]] in Malawi.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/715440/senegal-burundi|title=Burundi v Senegal game report|date=9 September 2024}}</ref>

